# Trivy CVE ignore list
#
# Format:
#   CVE-XXXX-XXXXX  # Reason. Accepted: YYYY-MM-DD  Review: YYYY-MM-DD
#
# Do not add entries without:
#   1. A documented reason
#   2. An accepted date
#   3. A review date (max 90 days out)
#
# ── Nuclei binary (usr/local/bin/nuclei) ─────────────────────────────────────
#
# These CVEs are in Nuclei v3.8.0's own Go module dependencies. We are on the
# latest stable release — no patched version is available upstream yet.
# Review dates are short (30 days) — upgrade Nuclei as soon as a fix ships.
#
# CVE-2026-34040: docker/docker v28.3.3 auth bypass — Nuclei uses this library
#   internally, not as a daemon. Not reachable through our scan workflow.
CVE-2026-34040  # Nuclei dep: docker/docker auth bypass. No upstream fix in Nuclei yet. Accepted: 2026-05-12  Review: 2026-06-12

# CVE-2026-45022: go-git improper parsing — Nuclei clones templates from
#   ProjectDiscovery's official repo only. No user-controlled git input.
CVE-2026-45022  # Nuclei dep: go-git parsing issue. No upstream fix in Nuclei yet. Accepted: 2026-05-12  Review: 2026-06-12

# CVE-2026-29181: OTel baggage header DoS — internal observability SDK,
#   not exposed to network input in our deployment.
CVE-2026-29181  # Nuclei dep: OTel DoS via baggage header. No upstream fix in Nuclei yet. Accepted: 2026-05-12  Review: 2026-06-12

